This paper proposes a new metric learning framework for classification, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. The paper also discusses the relationship between metric learning and Lipschitz functions, which is a topic in optimization and analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also includes experiments on popular datasets, which suggests that it may belong to cs.SD (Sound) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as well.
